result.execSummary:
The defendant Julius Daron Gonzalez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Julius Daron Gonzalez is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Julius Daron Gonzalez was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Julius Daron Gonzalez in court with attorney Darryl E Smith.  Paul Hauer for Antonella Aleman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defense motion to dismiss the criminal complaint is reviewed and argued by both Defense and the State.  Defense motion to dismiss is denied by the Court at this time.Preliminary hearing proceeded. Case is adjourned to Judge Siefert, Branch 47 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 5, 2014 at 08:30 am.
